FT  05 MAY 93 / International Company News: USAir offering raises Dollars
231m
USAir, the US carrier in which British Airways invested Dollars 300m for a
19.9 per cent voting interest earlier this year, has raised a net Dollars
231m from its sale of new ordinary shares at Dollars 20.75 per share. The
underwriters exercised their over- allotment options and a total 11.5m new
shares were sold.
In addition to the money from the offering USAir will receive another
Dollars 99.2m from British Airways - bringing the total raised to around
Dollars 330m.
